The paper deals with visual odometry, which is a topic in robotics (cs.RO) and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a novel system that combines direct and feature-based techniques, which involves machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The system is designed to perform in real-time, which involves control systems (cs.SY).
